# .env.prod.example — template for PROD-ONLY operations (gitignored real file: .env.prod)
#
# ⚠ THIS FILE IS TRACKED BY GIT — use PLACEHOLDER values only. Put REAL secrets in `.env.prod`
#   (gitignored), NEVER here.
#
# WHY THIS EXISTS
#   Local `.env` points DATABASE_URL at `localhost/ronindojo_prodsnap` and has the dev/baseline
#   Resend sender — NOT the prod Neon DB or the BBL sender. So one-off PROD operations (the claim
#   dogfood: setup-test-claimant.ts, send-bbl-truelson-thankyou.ts) need prod overrides.
#
#   Putting those overrides in a gitignored `.env.prod` means you NEVER paste secrets on the command
#   line (no creds in shell scrollback, no creds leaked into chat/transcripts).
#
# USAGE
#   cp .env.prod.example .env.prod      # then fill REAL values in .env.prod (the real file is gitignored)
#   bun --env-file=.env.prod scripts/setup-test-claimant.ts --send --node-slug chayce-johnson
#   bun --env-file=.env.prod scripts/send-bbl-truelson-thankyou.ts --verify
#
#   `--env-file=.env.prod` is an OVERLAY: the keys below win; everything else still falls back to `.env`.
#   So this file stays tiny — only the prod deltas, never a copy of `.env`.
#
# SECURITY
#   These are LIVE production credentials when filled in `.env.prod`. Rotate them if ever exposed
#   (Neon console reset; Resend dashboard revoke+reissue). NEVER commit the real `.env.prod`.

# Prod Postgres (Neon pooled connection string)
DATABASE_URL='postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@HOST-pooler.REGION.aws.neon.tech/neondb?sslmode=require&channel_binding=require'

# Resend — BBL transactional sender (distinct from the baseline RESEND_SENDER_EMAIL in .env).
# RESEND_API_KEY only needed if your prod Resend account differs from .env's (omit otherwise — the
# sender email is usually the only BBL-specific delta).
RESEND_API_KEY='re_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx'
RESEND_SENDER_EMAIL_BBL='welcome@blackbeltlegacy.com'
